# Sigil CODEOWNERS
#
# Single-trunk model: all PRs target `main`. Reviewers are auto-requested per the
# rules below. The `main-protection` ruleset enforces "review by code owner" for
# matched paths — see `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`.
#
# Today (pre-mainnet, single dev): @Kaleb-Rupe is the sole owner everywhere.
#
# WHEN a 2nd permanent maintainer joins, change `@Kaleb-Rupe` on critical paths
# (`programs/sigil/`, `sdk/kit/src/`, `.github/workflows/`) to a 2-person team
# (e.g. `@Sigil-Trade/maintainers`). Branch protection's "require N reviewers"
# automatically jumps to 2 the moment the team has ≥2 members. This is the
# Drift/MarginFi pattern for graceful escalation without ruleset changes.
#
# WHEN mainnet ships, also add the path-filtered "Required reviewers" rule to
# the `main-protection` ruleset — covered in pre-mainnet checklist in
# `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md` (Squads V4 multisig migration milestone).

# Default fallback — catches anything not matched below
*                                  @Kaleb-Rupe

